sequenceDiagram
    actor Maria
    participant Agent as Agent (Opus)
    participant LLM as LLM API
    participant Tools as Built-in Tools
    participant MCP as MCP (Odoo / Hetzner / Gmail / Cal)
    participant Subs as Sub-Agents

    Maria->>Agent: "Requirements doc for my Italian webshop,<br/>FR+BE, 2000 users, Hetzner, use my Odoo data"

    Note over Agent: Load memory + discover MCP tools<br/>(Odoo local, Hetzner/Gmail/Calendar remote)

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 1 — Understand
    Agent->>LLM: call #1 (prompt + tool schemas)
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: Read("templates/requirements.md")
    Agent->>Tools: Read template
    Tools-->>Agent: template structure

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 2 — Collect business data
    Agent->>LLM: call #2
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: mcp__odoo__get_metrics
    Agent->>Maria: Permission gate (sensitive business data)
    Maria-->>Agent: Approved
    Agent->>MCP: Odoo: orders, catalog, revenue, peaks
    MCP-->>Agent: 150 orders/day, 1200 products, 45K€/mo, peak ×3 Dec

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 3 — Parallel research (3 sub-agents)
    Agent->>LLM: call #3
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: Agent x3

    par Functional Analyst (Haiku)
        Agent->>Subs: "Find functional requirements for food e-commerce"
        Subs->>LLM: WebSearch food regulations, payment, delivery
        Subs-->>Agent: 32 functional requirements
    and Non-Functional Analyst (Haiku)
        Agent->>Subs: "Find NFR for 2000-user e-commerce"
        Subs->>LLM: WebSearch performance, GDPR, accessibility
        Subs-->>Agent: 15 non-functional requirements
    and Cloud Architect (Opus → spawns C1 + C2)
        Agent->>Subs: "Size Hetzner infra for 2000 users with Odoo data"
        Subs->>MCP: C1: Odoo volumetry → 50 req/s, 4vCPU needed
        Subs->>MCP: C2: Hetzner API → CPX31 9.29€, LB 5.49€
        Subs-->>Agent: 2×CPX31 + LB ≈ 25-45€/mo
    end

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 4 — Write document
    Agent->>LLM: call #4 (all results assembled)
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_call: Write("output/requirements.md")
    Agent->>Tools: Write 5 sections, 47 requirements
    Tools-->>Agent: OK

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 5 — Validate structure
    Agent->>Tools: Bash: validate-doc-structure.sh
    Tools-->>Agent: All sections present, requirements numbered

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 6 — Distribute
    Agent->>LLM: call #6
    LLM-->>Agent: tool_calls: mcp__gmail + mcp__calendar
    Agent->>Maria: Permission gate (send email + create event)
    Maria-->>Agent: Approved
    Agent->>MCP: Gmail: send draft to maria@bottega.it
    Agent->>MCP: Calendar: Tuesday 2pm review with tech partner
    MCP-->>Agent: email sent + event created

    Note over Agent,LLM: Turn 7 — Conclude
    Agent->>LLM: call #7
    LLM-->>Agent: final summary
    Agent->>Maria: "Done: 5 sections, 47 requirements,<br/>Hetzner 2×CPX31+LB ≈25-45€/mo,<br/>sent by email, review Tuesday 2pm"
    Note over Agent: Save memory: Maria's project profile
